PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard Screen
MARKER: dashboard_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing all categories and their balances
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category with its name, balance, and a pie chart, and a floating add category button in the bottom right.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #user
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and limit. The new category appears in the dashboard with a default balance of 0.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates the balance of a category
TAGS: #form, #user
---
When the user taps the edit icon on a category, a form appears. The user adjusts the balance and saves. The category's balance and pie chart update on the dashboard.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: ensure categories do not exceed their limits
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If a category's balance reaches its limit, no further expenses can be added to that category until the next month.

SURFACE: Category Name
MARKER: category_name
INTENT: label for the category name input
TAGS: #form, #input
---
The add category form has a label "Category Name" for the input field.

SURFACE: Balance Input
MARKER: balance_input
INTENT: label for the balance input field
TAGS: #form, #input, #user
---
The add category form has a label "Balance" for the input field where the user sets the initial balance.

SURFACE: Limit Input
MARKER: limit_input
INTENT: label for the limit input field
TAGS: #form, #input, #user
---
The add category form has a label "Limit" for the input field where the user sets the monthly limit.